OL,3,CInquiry vows to find truth about how
OL,4,Cdeadliest Channel crossing occurred
OL,6,FA former judge has warned there will
OL,7,Fbe "no place for obstruction or foot
OL,8,Fdragging" as he opened an inquiry into
OL,9,Fthe Channel's deadliest migrant
OL,10,Fcrossings tragedy on record.
OL,12,FSir Ross Cranston said the purpose of
OL,13,Fthe independent probe, announced by
OL,14,FTransport Secretary Mark Harper in
OL,15,FJanuary, was to find out the "truth"
OL,16,Fof what happened when at least 27
OL,17,Fpeople died as an inflatable boat
OL,18,Fcapsized while attempting the journey
OL,19,Fto the UK on November 24 2021.
