OL,3,CInquiry vows to find truth about how
OL,4,Cdeadliest Channel crossing occurred
OL,6,FThe inquiry chairman, an ex-High Court
OL,7,Fjudge and former solicitor general,
OL,8,Ftold a hearing in London on Wednesday
OL,9,Fthe proceedings would ascertain who
OL,10,Fthe people who died were, and when,
OL,11,Fwhere, and in what circumstances they
OL,12,Fcame to their deaths, as well as
OL,13,Fconsidering "what lessons can be
OL,14,Flearned" from the incident and what
OL,15,Frecommendations could be made to
OL,16,F"reduce the risk of a similar event
OL,17,Foccurring".
